I'm sorry. The more I think about it, the more I think the API should return an array of maps with named keys:
```json
{
  "mounts": [
    {
      "id": "04e4c255269ed2545e7f8bd1395a75f7949c50c223415c00c1d54bfa20f3b3d9",
      "mountpoint": "/var/lib/containers/storage/overlay/a078925828f57e20467ca31cfca8a849210d21ec7e5757332b72b6924f441c17/merged"
    },
    {
      "id": "1d58c319f9e881a644a5122ff84419dccf6d138f744469281446ab243ef38924",
      "mountpoint": "/var/lib/containers/storage/overlay/948fcf93f8cb932f0f03fd52e3180a58627d547192ffe3b88e0013b98ddcd0d2/merged"
    }
  ]
}
```
My reasons are:
* Consistency. Other interfaces (e.g. `ListImages`, `ListContainers`) return such structures;
* Friendliness. Varlink offers excellent discoverability; this small change makes it slightly easier for someone to understand what `ListContainerMounts` is providing; and
* Paranoia: should there ever be a situation in which one container is associated with multiple mount points, an array will handle it perfectly.

Again I'm really sorry to be causing this trouble. I just think those small changes make it likelier to "get it right", and hence less likelier that it'll need to be revisited in the future.
